Add a CMake custom (pseudo) target, backed by a script under cmake/scripts/, that reads the JSON tags file produced by the `ctags-json` target from goal 03 ($BUILDDIR/generated/ctags/tags.json), extracts every struct and class symbol together with its enclosing namespace, and writes the result to $BUILDDIR/generated/class_names.json so the class inventory can be consumed by the printer-generation step (goal 05). It is part of the generation chain that the build runs only when its input is newer or its output is missing; the refresh is kicked off manually via `ctags-json`.
